<item>
            <title>[SPARK-4495] Memory leak in JobProgressListener due to `spark.ui.retainedJobs` not being used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-4495</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the JobProgressListener, we never actually remove jobs from the jobIdToData map. In fact, there&apos;s a somewhat embarrassing typo: &lt;em&gt;retailed&lt;/em&gt; jobs:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;  val retailedJobs = conf.getInt(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;spark.ui.retainedJobs&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, DEFAULT_RETAINED_JOBS)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was introduced by my patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2321&quot; title=&quot;Design a proper progress reporting &amp;amp; event listener API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-2321&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-2321&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: I should have added a test that set &lt;tt&gt;spark.ui.retainedJobs&lt;/tt&gt; to some low threshold and checked that we only reported information for that many jobs; there was already a corresponding &quot;test LRU eviction of stages&quot; test that I should have just copied and modified.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This only affects the unreleased 1.2.0 version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
